      "content": "A loud humming sound with no spinning blades on your AC unit could be a few things, like a seized motor or a capacitor issue. It's generally best to exercise caution, so before you go out there, it's safer to turn off the power to the unit at the breaker box. If you're not comfortable diagnosing it, calling a professional HVAC technician is the wisest course of action.",
